  "body": "- [âˆš ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## truffle-contract does not type-check parameters\r\n\r\nWhen I've a contract constructor accepting a specific parameter my tests don't not fail if I pass to the constructor something not expected.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate a simple contract like:\r\n```\r\ncontract Contract {\r\n    bool paused;\r\n    function Contract(bool _status) {\r\n        paused = _status\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nand try on the tests to do something like that:\r\n```\r\n// I expected it would fail but it isn't\r\n    it(\"should not be created passing strange value to constructor\", async () => {\r\n         try {\r\n             const c = await Contract.new('hello')\r\n         } catch(e) {\r\n             console.error(`Error: ${e}`)\r\n         }\r\n     })\r\n```\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nCatch any kind of error\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nTx receipt\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macosx\r\n* Ethereum client: truffle develop\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Truffle v4.1.5\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v9.10.1\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 5.8.0\r\n",
